 orbiters of both Ceres and Vesta and conclude that\ndecametre-sized objects detected in the vicinity of Vesta by the DAWN mission\nmay, in fact, belong to this dynamical class rather than be bona-fide (i.e.\nkeplerian) satellites of Vesta.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Oct 2011 14:58:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-30"}
